WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:26.240
Admin approval and payment unlock: The right booking is approved, the customer is notified, and payment is unlocked without skipping verification.

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:43.320
Booking queue: Each request is approved, declined, opened, or assigned one next action.

00:00:43.320 --> 00:01:02.840
Booking lifecycle: The operator knows the screen, tab, and gate for each status change.

00:01:02.840 --> 00:01:17.240
Fleet and availability: Vehicles shown to customers are truly available, priced, visible, clean, and not blocked.

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:35.440
Pickup, return, and check-ins: The day has a clean queue: blocked pickups, handoffs, due-back, overdue, active out, and returned settlement.

00:01:35.440 --> 00:01:55.800
Payments, deposits, and refunds: Every money action is tied to the right booking, amount, reason, and audit trail.

00:01:55.800 --> 00:02:13.960
Insurance review: Coverage is approved, rejected, or escalated before the vehicle leaves.

00:02:13.960 --> 00:02:29.600
Customers, portal, and long-term: Support, renewal, billing, and long-term actions stay tied to the right customer.

00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:45.360
Messaging and notifications: One customer receives one clear action, tied to one booking or account reason.

00:02:45.360 --> 00:03:01.200
Revenue and reporting: The operator can identify performance signals and decide the next business action.

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:20.560
Settings and system health: The operator knows whether the issue is workflow, provider, notification, or configuration.
